{
  "stem": "7506.7",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, he got me a job in South Africa, as a beautician, in a-- in the top place in Johannesburg, where he lived.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "For a while I lived with them, with his wife and his two boys.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I got a place of my own.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And South Africa was a wonderful place in those days.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I was in South Africa, [PAUSES] women who I used to attend upon always had either daughters or they had nieces or I know some-- [PAUSES] all that's what you call the Yiddishe business.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I can't bear that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I really cannot bear that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I've never been able to bear that, because indeed, when I lived in England, my stepfather used to say, oh, I do business with a man.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He's got-- I'm going to get you-- always.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I-- I used to cringe from all that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "One day, I was at my uncle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "His name was also Sam Rabbe-- all the same family.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was at his house, and he had invited over a business colleague of his, with his wife and a daughter.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES] You know, and she wasn't-- she wasn't bad, sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And by that time-- let me think.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In 1958, I was [PAUSES] 26.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES] I'd learnt a little bit about the opposite sex by then, [PAUSES] maybe more than was good for me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And I met this girl who had just come out of university in Johannesburg, lived outside Johannesburg in a small town.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And what may seem strange, the father was-- in America, you would call a rancher.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In English, you would call a farmer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And strangely enough, there are a lot-- the biggest farms in South Africa were Jewish people, people whose parents had come from Eastern Europe.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
